> Looking for a quick and tasty midweek dinner option? Try cooking up our Thai Green Style Chicken Curry in just 15 minutes for a delicious and speedy meal.

Boil a half-full #kettle{}. Pour it into a #saucepan{} with @salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat.

Boil the @Jasmine Rice{150%g}, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain, pop back in the pan and cover.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a saucepan on medium-high heat.

Once hot, fry the @Thai Green Style Paste{45%g}, ~{30%seconds}.

Next, stir in the @Coconut Milk{200%ml}, @Chicken Stock Paste{10%g} and @Water for the Sauce{50%ml}.

Add the @Diced British Chicken Breast{260%g}. Bring to the boil, then lower the heat.

Simmer, ~{10-12%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat. Cook so there's no pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, halve the @Lime{1}.

Once thickened, add the @Baby Spinach{40%g} to the curry in handfuls, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Squeeze in some lime juice. Add a splash of water if it's too thick.

Taste and season with salt, pepper and more lime juice if needed.

Fluff up the rice and share between your bowls.

Top with the curry.

Sprinkle over the @Chilli Flakes{1%pinch}.

> Add less chilli flakes if you'd prefer things milder.

Cut any remaining lime into wedges for squeezing over.

Enjoy!